content:
Specify the Chat Settings for Your Embedded Chat Deployment

Embedded Chat uses a Chat deployment ID and button. The Chat configuration details that you provide are used to generate the chat code snippet that you add to your web pages.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.
To set up Embedded Chat: Customize Application AND Modify Metadata

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. Ensure that you have a Chat deployment and a Chat button available to use with Embedded Chat.

From Setup, select Embedded Service.
Select the Embedded Service deployment and click View.
In the Embedded Service configuration page, go to the Chat settings section and click Start.
Select the Chat configuration from the dropdown list.
Select the Chat button or automated invitation from the dropdown list.
Select Show queue position if desired.
Make sure that the Chat button has Enable Queue selected in your Chat button settings.
Click Save.

After providing the Chat settings, get the code to add the chat window to your web pages.
title: Configuring Embedded Chat Settings in Service Cloud
